<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,917,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,917,942]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Recognition</emphasis>
. Large species of the 
<emphasis box="[604,896,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">P. pallidiventris-cursitans</emphasis>
group; occiput with 
<number box="[1142,1156,918,942]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" value="1.0">1</number>
pair yellowish inclinate verticals; antenna largely yellow, postpedicel darkened on apical part, about 
<number box="[1072,1107,953,978]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X longer than wide; palpus yellowish, large, oval; mesonotum densely golden grey pollinose, with yellowish bristles, 
<number box="[1261,1275,990,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" value="2.0">2</number>
notopleurals, katepisternum with polished black patch occupying about 
<number box="[852,862,1026,1050]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[873,887,1026,1050]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" value="3.0">3</number>
of its size; legs almost entirely yellow, only tarsomeres indistinctly annulated; mid tibia with long pointed apical spur; abdomen entirely yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
